citation.case_name: NORTHWESTERN PACIFIC RAILROAD CO. v. Interstate Commerce Commission

html:
379 U.S. 132

85 S.Ct. 274

13 L.Ed.2d 333

NORTHWESTERN PACIFIC RAILROAD CO.
v.
INTERSTATE COMMERCE COMMISSION et al.

No. 381.

Supreme Court of the United States

November 23, 1964

Rehearing Denied Jan. 18, 1965.

See 379 U.S. 984, 85 S.Ct. 641.

Randolph Karr, for appellant.

Solicitor General Cox, Assistant Attorney General Orrick, Robert B. Hummel, Arthur J. Murphy, Jr., and Robert W. Ginnane, for appellees Interstate Commerce Commission and others.

J. Thomason Phelps, for appellees Public Utilities Commission of California and others.

Boris H. Lakusta, for appellees City of San Rafael and others.

Frederick G. Pfrommer, for appellee Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway Co.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motions to affirm are granted and the judgment is affirmed.
